{
  "text": "A plasmid containing S100A4 cDNA was purchased from OBIO Biotechnology Company. S100A4-specific siRNAs were synthesized as previously described [CITATION_1] .Exponential growth phase cells were planted in 6-well plates at a density of 0.5x10 5 cells/mL and starved for 24 hours, then 1mg of siRNA or 4ug cDNA in reduced serum medium were transfected(OPTI-MEM I; Invitrogen) according to the manufacturer's protocol.",
